 from nigel allen subject results of gusto heart attack study to be released friday reply to nigel allen organization canada remote systems distribution sci lines six one here is a press release from medical science communications results of gusto heart attack study to be released friday to assignment desk medical writer contact jim augustine of medical science communication seven zero three six four four six eight two four or steve hull or tracy furey eight zero zero four seven seven nine six two six or april two nine three zero two zero two three nine three two zero zero zero or two zero two six six two seven five nine two j w marriott news advisory results of the largest heart attack study ever undertaken the global utilization of streptokinase and t pa for occluded coronary arteries trial gusto will be presented friday april three zero at the clinical research meeting a press conference will be held at one two three zero p m gusto evaluates the most aggressive emergency room treatment strategies available to clear blocked heart arteries and restore blood flow to the heart a process called thrombolysis the thrombolytic strategies compared in gusto use powerful drugs to break up blood clots in heart vessels quickly and prevent clots from recurring these strategies have never been compared directly in a large scale clinical trial until gusto the results are expected to have an important impact on heart attack treatment worldwide the press conference will be held at two locations live at the national press club main lounge one three th floor five two nine one four th st n w washington d c and via satellite at the hotel macklowe one four five w four four th street four th floor new york city between broadway and six th avenue gusto results will be presented by eric topol m d gusto study chairman professor and chairman of the department of cardiology at the cleveland clinic foundation robert califf m d clinical director gusto coordinating center and associate professor of medicine at duke university medical center and allan ross m d coordinator of the gusto angiographic substudy and professor and director of the division of cardiology at the george washington university medical center editorial notes attention television the press conference may be viewed in its entirety via satellite starting at one two three zero p m edt c band telestar three zero two transponder two v dual audio six two six eight or kusbs six transponder eight following the press conference there will be a news package and b roll feed camera ready illustrations also will be available at the press conference telephone hook up to the press conference is planned availability is limited please call mcs for more information for reporters who will be at the sheraton washington attending the clinical research meeting on friday morning minibus transportation will be provided to the press conference the bus will depart at one two p m it also will be available for return to the sheraton after the press conference for more information contact steve hull or tracy furey of mcs for the gusto study group at eight zero zero four seven seven nine six two six or at the j w marriott april two nine to april three zero at two zero two three nine three two zero zero zero or two zero two six six two seven five nine two for more information about the clinical research meeting contact jim augustine of medical science communications at seven zero three six four four six eight two four three zero canada remote systems toronto ontario four one six six two nine seven zero zero zero six two nine seven zero four four